page.title: 01BLOCK 05120156 _ REVIEW
page.content: Fetcham is a popular residential area.This may be because Fetcham is surrounded by mainly countryside and is peaceful.Many of the houses are quite old and some are of historic interest.A large area of the countryside is the wooded area of Bookham Common.Around it there is rough grazing used by the farms. In our block we have the River Mole and M-25.These both run across our block.At three points the R.Mole goes under the M-25.The river runs nearby most of the farms and is also good for leisure purposes.The M-25 is still under construction and should be finished soon. In our block we have many buildings other than residential houses. Interes _ting buildings include:Woodlands Park, Slyfield House, an old church and The Yehudi Menuhin School of Music
